  "title": "The excellence of asking for Allah's blessings upon the Prophet PBUH",
  "source": "Hisn al-Muslim 223",
  "arabic": "وَقَالَ صلى الله عليه وسلم مَا مِنْ أَحَدٍ يُسَلِّمُ عَلَيَّ إِلاَّ رَدَّ اللَّهُ عَلَيَّ رُوحِيَ حَتَّى أَرُدَّ عَلَيْهِ السَّلاَمَ",
  "meaning": "The Prophet [PBUH] said: 'No one sends greetings (or prayers of peace) upon me but Allah returns my soul to me so that I may return his greetings",
